          {
            "commit": "88f2129504f0530106ebdbe7f5ff918d03bfcb42",
            "subject": "LU-5912 libcfs: use vfs api for fsync calls"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-20 10:51:45.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
          "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-20 13:38:53.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-6266 libcfs: add kstrtoul() compat function",
        "message": "LU-6266 libcfs: add kstrtoul() compat function\n\nThe kstrtoul() function was only added to the upstream kernel in\ncommit v2.6.38-6934-g33ee3b2. While it is backported to RHEL6 2.6.32\nkernels, it does not exist for vanilla kernels before that point.\n\nThe patch http://review.whamcloud.com/5700 added uses of kstrtoul()\nto Lustre that break the build for older kernels.  While it would be\npossible to convert those calls to simple_strtoul(), that function\nis deprecated in newer kernels, and checkpatch.pl will generate a\nwarning, so using kstrtoul() is the right thing for newer kernels.\n\nAdd a wrapper function for kstrtoul() for older kernels.  There are\nmany other kstrto*() functions that are not added by this patch.\nOnly the one function call is currently used, though it would be good\nto convert Lustre over to using this family of functions instead of\nsimple_strtoul() in the future.\n\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/13820\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Id30313e51b8d240aacc09a6e86a22460fa08971b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
